# 🚀 CodePilot AI

> An AI-powered Software Engineering Assistant that understands GitHub repositories using semantic search and AI agents.

CodePilot AI is designed to help developers quickly understand unfamiliar codebases. It clones repositories, analyzes source code, generates embeddings, performs semantic search, and will eventually answer questions about any GitHub project using AI agents.

---

# 📖 Why CodePilot AI?

Understanding a new codebase is one of the most time-consuming tasks for developers.

Developers often spend hours searching through hundreds of files just to answer questions like:

- Where is authentication implemented?
- Which files handle database operations?
- How does the API flow work?
- Where is the payment logic?

CodePilot AI aims to solve this problem by converting an entire GitHub repository into an AI-searchable knowledge base.

---

# ✨ Features

## ✅ Repository Cloner
- Clone any public GitHub repository
- Automatic repository management
- GitPython integration
- FastAPI REST API
- Swagger documentation

---

## ✅ Repository Parser
- Recursively scan repository structure
- Ignore unnecessary directories (`.git`, `venv`, `node_modules`, etc.)
- Filter supported source code and configuration files
- Extract metadata for every file
- Parse repositories through a REST API

---

## 🚧 Repository Reader *(Current Work)*
- Safely read source code files
- UTF-8 support with error handling
- Prepare repository for code chunking

---

# 🏗️ Current Architecture

```text
GitHub Repository
        │
        ▼
Repository Cloner ✅
        │
        ▼
Repository Parser ✅
        │
        ▼
Repository Reader 🚧
        │
        ▼
Code Chunker
        │
        ▼
Embedding Generator
        │
        ▼
FAISS Vector Database
        │
        ▼
Semantic Search
        │
        ▼
AI Agents
```

